## QIIME2

QIIME is an open-source bioinformatics pipeline for performing microbiome analysis from raw DNA sequencing data. QIIME2 is a completely new and different version than QIIME1

## Basic Information
Installed: Aug, 2019

Updated: NA

Link: https://hpc.ilri.cgiar.org/qiime2-software

## Usage
You can check the available versions using:
`module qiime2/2019.7 `

Then you can load the required version using:
`module load qiime2/2019.7 `

## Installation
Install instructions available from:  https://hpc.ilri.cgiar.org/qiime2-software

```
cd /tmp
$ sudo mkdir /opt/apps/qiime2.1
$ sudo chown bmuganda:bmuganda /opt/apps/qiime2.1
$ wget https://repo.continuum.io/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh
$ bash Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh -p /opt/apps/qiim2.1/conda
$ source /opt/apps/qiime2/conda/bin/activate
$ conda update -n base conda
$ wget https://data.qiime2.org/distro/core/qiime2-2019.7-py35-linux-conda.yml
$ conda env create -p /opt/apps/qiime2.1/2019.7 --file qiime2-2019.7-py35-linux-conda.yml
$ conda activate /opt/apps/qiime2.1/2019.7
$ sudo chown -R root:root /opt/apps/qiime2.1
pt/apps/qiime2
$ qiime --help

```
